[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two women are charged with Londonderry attack

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two women have appeared at Londonderry Magistrates Court charged with attacking a man in the city on Sunday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The court was told that Samantha Kerrigan, 29, from Bonds Hill and Kim Hazlett, 18, from Francis Street were found in a flat with their clothes covered in blood following a row.
They are charged with inflicting grievous bodily harm with intent.
Both women were released on their own bail of Â£500 to appear in court again on 13 August.
They are also charged with false imprisonment and possessing a crutch and brush shaft with intent.
Ms Kerrigan is separately charged with attempting to suffocate, choke or strangle the victim.
